com.qti.snapdragon.sdk.digitalpen

Class DigitalPenManager.SideChannelData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qti.snapdragon.sdk.digitalpen.DigitalPenManager.SideChannelData
  • Enclosing class:
    DigitalPenManager

    public static class DigitalPenManager.SideChannelData
extends java.lang.Object
    This data is returned through listeners upon receiving pen events. This side-channel data differs from the Android MotionEvent in that it contains more information (e.g. tilt) and bypasses the android input framework.

    The position and tilt fields depend on the DigitalPenManager.SideChannelMapping parameter, set when calling DigitalPenManager.registerSideChannelEventListener(Area, OnSideChannelDataListener)

    When using DigitalPenManager.SideChannelMapping.RAW:

    • Position fields are 0.01mm units
    • Tilt fields describe a normalized 3D vector in Q30 format
    When using DigitalPenManager.SideChannelMapping.SCALED
    • Position fields are in logical units from 0 to MAX_LOGICAL_UNIT
    • Tilt fields xTilt and yTilt are deflection from the Z axis in degrees. zTilt is always 0.
    See Also:
    DigitalPenManager.OnSideChannelDataListener, DigitalPenManager.registerSideChannelEventListener(Area, OnSideChannelDataListener), android.view.MotionEvent
